"title": "5137: bones",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5137",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Associated in Hebrew thought with both death and life. A symbol of the whole person, and also the state of one's well-being.</p>\n<h2>Bones represent dead bodies</h2>\n<h3>Human remains to be treated with respect</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:13\">1SA 31:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:12\">1CH 10:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:12-2Sam21:14\">2SA 21:12–21:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:31\">1KI 13:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:18\">2KI 23:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:15\">EZK 39:15</a></p>\n<h3>Non-burial as a sign of disrespect</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:1-Amos2:2\">AMO 2:1–2:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Non-burial as a sign of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps53:5\">PSA 53:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:34-2Kgs9:37\">2KI 9:34–9:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:7\">PSA 141:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:1-Jer8:2\">JER 8:1–8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:4-Ezek24:5\">EZK 24:4–24:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:10\">EZK 24:10</a></p>\n<h2>Bones were considered to be unclean</h2>\n<h3>Bones made anyone who touched them unclean</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:16\">NUM 19:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:18\">NUM 19:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:27\">MAT 23:27</a></p>\n<h3>Bones used to desecrate objects of pagan worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:14\">2KI 23:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:2\">1KI 13:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:16\">2KI 23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:20\">2KI 23:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:5\">2CH 34:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:5\">EZK 6:5</a></p>\n<h2>Bones as a sign of hope</h2>\n<h3>The hope of God's promise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:25\">GEN 50:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:19\">EXO 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:32\">JOS 24:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:22\">HEB 11:22</a> <em>The presence of Joseph's bones among the Israelites was a constant reminder of God's promise to Joseph concerning the promised land.</em></p>\n<h3>The hope of life after death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:1-Ezek37:14\">EZK 37:1–37:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:21\">2KI 13:21</a></p>\n<h3>The hope of the Passover lamb</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:36\">JHN 19:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:46\">EXO 12:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:12\">NUM 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:20\">PSA 34:20</a> <em>Jesus Christ fulfilled the symbolism of the unbroken bones of the Passover lamb.</em></p>\n<h2>Bones represent living individuals</h2>\n<h3>Bones indicate a living body</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:39\">LUK 24:39</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Bones represent a whole person</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:10\">PSA 35:10</a></strong> <em>“My whole being” is literally “my bones”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:4-Job2:5\">JOB 2:4–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:11\">JOB 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:2\">PSA 6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:7-Ps51:8\">PSA 51:7–51:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:14\">ISA 66:14</a></p>\n<h3>Bones represent kinship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:23\">GEN 2:23</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:14\">GEN 29:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:2\">JDG 9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:1\">2SA 5:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:1\">1CH 11:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:12-2Sam19:13\">2SA 19:12–19:13</a></p>\n<h2>Bones represent physical health</h2>\n<h3>Bones associated with good health</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:30\">PRO 15:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:7-Prov3:8\">PRO 3:7–3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:24\">PRO 16:24</a></p>\n<h3>Bones symbolise strength and vigour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:23-Job21:24\">JOB 21:23–21:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:11\">JOB 20:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:18\">JOB 40:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:15\">PRO 25:15</a></p>\n<h3>Bones associated with God's protection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:19-Ps34:20\">PSA 34:19–34:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:36\">JHN 19:36</a></p>\n<h3>Mere skin and bone represents bad health</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:20\">JOB 19:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:21\">JOB 33:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:5\">PSA 102:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:8\">LAM 4:8</a></p>\n<h3>Broken bones symbolise defeat or oppression</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:8\">NUM 24:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:13\">ISA 38:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:17\">JER 50:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:4\">LAM 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:24\">DAN 6:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:2-Mic3:3\">MIC 3:2–3:3</a></p>\n<h3>Health can be damaged by negative attitudes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:30\">PRO 14:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:14\">JOB 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:4\">PRO 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:22\">PRO 17:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:16\">HAB 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Health can be damaged by sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:3\">PSA 38:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:3\">PSA 32:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:18\">PSA 109:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:13\">LAM 1:13</a></p>\n<h3>Repentance brings restoration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:2\">PSA 6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:18\">PSA 51:18</a></p>\n<h3>Health can be damaged through obedience to God's will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:9\">JER 23:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:17\">JOB 30:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:19\">JOB 33:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:14\">PSA 22:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:17\">PSA 22:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:10\">PSA 31:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:10\">PSA 42:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:9\">JER 20:9</a></p>",
